\title{Closure of a set is smallest closed set containing it}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-12}
\taxon{proposition}

\p{Let #{(X,\mathcal{T})} be a [[gt-0002]]. Let #{E\subset X} be a subset of #{X}. Then for any [closed set](gt-000E) #{F\subset X} such that #{E\subset F}, we have the [closure](gt-000G) of #{E} also be a subset #{\closure{E}\subset F}.}
